history.text: Hello!
Hello!
The movie I chose is Inception, it's a really great movie; I haven't seen it in a while though.
Do you know the name of a good movie?
Oh, OK. What is it about?
It's about these two guys, Dominick and Arthur, who use experimental medical technology to enter the subconscious of their targets in order to get information that they want.
Is it funny? or is it more adventure filled?
Definitely more adventure filled, the genre isn't really based around humor. It's more of an action/thriller but it's great if you like that kind of thing.
That sounds very interesting! Maybe I will check it out.
It has Leonardo DeCaprio, right?
yup he plays the main character Dominick Cobb
Him and the other guy Arthur end up doing this sequence of quest where they enter people's dreams.
I remember hearing a lot about it. I don't know why I haven't seen it yet.
haha, yeah it was a really famous movie for a while
I actually feel bad when I mention it as one of my favorite movies as I feel like i'm just choosing something popular but it was a great brain twister
You shouldn't feel bad. I just sometimes miss a lot of movies. I know it supposed to be a very good one.
I like movies that make you think a little, so I think I would like it.

So there is this businessman named Saito who tries to get Dom to start putting ideas in people's subconscious. They want to break up the energy conglomerate of their competitor named Fisher. So Saito wants Dom to convince Fischers son/heir to destroy the company by infiltrating his subconscious.
Yeah, movies that make me think are my favorite

The movie is all about like technology interfering with
 dreams
I can't really think of anything similar
Do you generally watch highly rated movies?
Very cool. I tend to see "indie" movies most, I guess. I'm sure this qualifies!
hahaha oh well yeah this isn't really an indie movie
it's just one of the top popular movies so if you're more into indie it makes sense you didn't watch this
I do know that technology interfered with my dreams when I first played tetris
Hahahhaa, howso?
Oh, I would dream about playing tetris, and see the little shapes. I'm not young, so tetris was a big game when I was growing up. We played a lot
Ahhhh I mean I still like playing tetris
I'm not super young but it was still fun in my generation
I've played battle tetris before, have you?
I guess it is a classic. I don't think so. Is that where you play against another person? If so, I'm sure that I have
Yeah, it's when you play against someone and when you clear rows it makes the bottom of their screen get added rows
oh I should go back to inception, It's also a love story if you like that haha
Yep. That's fun too. Now I want to watch Inception and then play tetris
it makes it so people who aren't that into sci fi like it too
ahahhahaha
you can do both at the same time
Ha! I like some sci-fi. Mostly the older stuff? I haven't seen them all, but it's interesting.
Thanks for chatting!
Haha thanks to you as well!
